        "description": "Custom Concert Workflow (authored using the same block schema as IBM's published Maven_Package_Upgrade sample) that automates remediation of a specific, known code-risk finding: CWE-89 SQL Injection in VulnerableSearchRepository.java, caused by string-concatenated SQL. Not a catalogued CVE, so it falls outside Trivy's SCA scanning - this represents the 'unknown'/non-CVE remediation path, raised as a Git PR just like the log4j CVE fix.",
